<!-- EDIT1 SECTION "FAQ:" [1-20] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit2"><a name="how_do_i_change_my_player_name" id="how_do_i_change_my_player_name">How do I change my player name?</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
 Depending on which player you are, you use p#_name to change your name. <a href="doku.php?id=main:general_docs:faq:usage:general:console" class="wikilink1" title="main:general_docs:faq:usage:general:console">open the console</a>, and type:
</p>
<pre class="code">p0_name &quot;My Name&quot;</pre>

<p>
By default, your player number is 0 (zero). However, if you are using splitscreen, the player on the left is p0 and the player on the right is p1. You can also add this into <a href="doku.php?id=main:general_docs:faq:usage:general:config" class="wikilink1" title="main:general_docs:faq:usage:general:config">config.cfg</a> so that gusanos has this settings every time you run it.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT2 SECTION "How do I change my player name?" [21-527] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit3"><a name="how_do_i_make_my_name_multicoloured" id="how_do_i_make_my_name_multicoloured">How do I make my name multicoloured?</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
When changing your name, you can put in formatting controls. By pressing Control + K, you put in a little symbol of an arrow pointing downwards. You then put any of the following numbers after it:
01 02 03 04 05 06 07 08 09 10 11 12 13 14 15
Where 01 is black, and the bright colours are first, with them getting darker in the two digit numbers. To get a listing of all the different colours, bring up the speech box with F1, and replace the K in the following text with the control and k symbol:
</p>
<pre class="code">k0101k0202k0303k0404k0505k0606k0707k0808k0909k1010k1111k1212k1313k1414k1515</pre>

</div>
<!-- EDIT3 SECTION "How do I make my name multicoloured?" [528-] --></div>
